  "texts": [
    "To fill the gap between existing code generation tasks and practical coding scenarios, we formalize the repo-level code generation task.",
    "Since a code repository generally contains intricate invocation relationships, only with a deep understanding of the code repository can LLMs generate satisfying programs that not only adhere to requirements but also seamlessly integrate with the current repository.",
    "Given a code repository, the repo-level code generation task aims to generate code based on all the software artifacts included in the repository, encompassing the documentation, code dependency, runtime environment, which form the task input.",
    "Here we give a detailed description of its composition format.",
    "Figure 1 shows an illustration of the repo-level code generation task."
